title.narrative: Power Transmission Project in Support of the Energy Sector Reform & Development Program

description.narrative: The overall program objective is to improve the security, reliability and quality of energy supply, and, therefore, facilitateunimpeded operation of the energy market, both domestically and internationally. The main objective of the Power TransmissionProject is to improve the security, reliability and quality of power supply through the rehabilitation of transmission substationsand the strengthening of the power transmission network. The project will also aim to improve institutional capacity and technicalcapabilities of transmission system operator, UkrEnergo (UE), so that it can assure secure and reliable operation of the highvoltage power grid, and, therefore, facilitate unimpeded operation and opening up of the electricity market.

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, D (1) | Description :Borrower to maintain throughout life of project CESRD | Frequency :Yearly

Component E: Implementation of Grid Code.

target.value: Finalization and approval of the Grid Code by the Respective Authority

actual.value: NERC approval expected after the Grid Code is revised according to the approved WEM Law (which is also under revision perrequirements of Energy Community Secretariat to align this law to requirements of 3rd EU Energy Package). Updated WEM law is to besubmitted to the Parliament at the end of 2015 early 2016.

title.narrative: Support sustainable economic development by improving security, reliability, efficiency and quality of energy supply through investments (rehabilitation and strengthening of transmission network)

baseline.value: Estimated Energy not served due to transm. system failures: 747.3 GWh Transmission losses: 3.4% Voltage quality:voltage outsideaccept. range (+/-5% of the nominal voltage) in several substations

target.value: Energy not served reduced by at least 35 GWh/year Transmission losses reduced by 14 MW; Voltage within acceptable range inallsubstations included in the project.

actual.value: Continued progress under contracts for Dniper and Donbas Power Grids including installation of high voltage circuit breakers for750kV SS and Protective Relaying and Automation. Currently Contracts UE/001/1 and UE/001/3 are completed and almost closed two morecontracts UE/003 and UE/003A on High Voltage Circuit Breakers for 750 kV SS and Contract UE/004 on Protective relaying andAutomation for 750 kV SS in Dnieper and Donbass Power Grids. Other contracts are under implementation. More time is needed tocomplete remaining contracts.

target.value: Operation of 330 kV 73 km TL to Dniester and 330 kV Bar s/s

title.narrative: Component C: Stabilization of the Crimea electric power grid

baseline.value: Low reliability and quality of power supply.

target.value: Simferopol s/s is not completed due to force-majeure event in the project area.

actual.value: Simferopol s/s is not completed due to force-majeure event in the project area.

target.value: Finalization of TA in Capacity building in procurement and project management and in annual auditing of project and company accounts

actual.value: Has been moved to the Second Power Transmission Project, due for Board approval on December 22, 2014.

title.narrative: Component A: Rehabilitation of Transmission Substations

target.value: Replacement of 11 power breakers at 750 kV s/sCompletion of reconstruction of 4 s/s 220 kV and 330 kVChaikino 330 kV s/s is notcompleted due to a force-majeure event in the project area.Completion of installation of relay protection systems and automationsystems at 750 kV s/s

actual.value: Contracts are signed and under implementation. Two out of 5 contracts two have been completed UE/001/1 and UE/001/3. Two othercontracts are under implementation UE/001/2 and UE/002/2 and one substation is not completed due to force-majeure event in theproject area.

title.narrative: Implementation of the Wholesale Electricity Market (WEM) concept

baseline.value: WEM concept adopted in 2002 but not implemented. Draft law on Operational Principles of Ukraine's Power Market

target.value: Development of Market rules, regulatory and legal framework of new energy market model

actual.value: Implmentation of the newly approved law has started, amendments under preparation. Implementation will be carried out by July 1,2017. On July 3 2015 MoECI presented jointly with Energy Community Secretariat an updated draft of the Wholesale Electricity MarketLaw, which has to be finalized by end of 2015, early 2016 and submitted/approved by Parliament. New WEM law is to be aligned withEU 3rd Energy Package.
